social_posts.post_text: Stairway in a recent project in Cheltenham. We used @farrowandball #hardwickwhite on the woodwork and stairs, paired with #schoolhousewhite on the walls. A sisal runner with black binding leads you up to the vignette at the top of the hall. We sourced the antique portrait from @vinterior and love it paired with a Gustavian demi-lune console. I think it is important to create a sense of arrival and destination in a hallway. We endeavour to do this in every home we design. 🖤🖤🌿 Photo by @chriswakefield.photography

A little behind the scenes moment. Go antiquing with me in Paris in under 30 seconds. We had such a fun weekend celebrating a friend’s birthday in my favourite city and managed to sneak in some sourcing for current and upcoming projects. 🖼️🪑🪞Who wants to come with me next time?

Wait for it… wait for it… We designed this bespoke bed-end bench to conceal a pop-up tv… a must-have for our clients in their bedroom. A clever way of incorporating a television into bedroom design without having it become the main focus. What do we think? 🤍🤍📺

A little twin room bedside moment in the Coach House at our Clifford House project. This was such a fun one to embark on as it was truly just a shell of a building when we arrived. We love working on refurbishments and developments… seeing the building become a home is so rewarding. The perfect guesthouse for the sweetest clients, an extension of the main home and the perfect place to host friends and family. We had the headboards and valances made in a fave @penny_morrison_ltd fabric and love how calm yet punchy the room feels. The bedside table is painted in @farrowandball #lighblue topped off with a fave chunky rattan lamp. Who’s excited to see the rest of this project? 🤍🤍 photo by @chriswakefield.photography

Corner of the kitchenette in our Coach House project in Somerset. This space links the two bedrooms and acts as the perfect mini kitchen for guests. We designed it to have a full-height cupboard which conceals the small appliances keeping the overall look clean and organised. A Carrara marble shelf allows for a moment of pretty display and a pair of @alicepalmerco wall light shades add the so needed softness and femininity to the room. Cabinets are painted @farrowandball #oldwhite and the t&g panelling is in #slippersatin photo by @chriswakefield.photography
Sweet little corner of a guest bedroom in our coach house project. We love a gingham and a ruffle. 🤍🤍 Perfect spot for a good 📖☕️

A little holiday inspiration from @vintageholiday 🎄🎄🧡💚 Absolutely love his layered dining room filled to the brim with splendour. Gives us all the merry feels! Colour is always a yes during the holidays and even chicer when it’s done in layers of vintage and antique one of a kind ornaments combined with our fave blue and white. His tree is divine! Is anyone else into the tinsel this year? It’s def making a comeback ✨✨

A little WFH moment! We had so much fun designing this gentleman’s study in a Georgian villa last year. Previously the dining room, this space had a doorway to the kitchen to the left of the fireplace. We closed it up and reinstated the symmetry of the room by designing alcove units either side of the chimney breast. The result is a cosy and practical study with plenty of space for books, printers and wifi kit! We even managed to squeeze in some concealed speakers to the back of the bookshelves. This room has all the amenities of a modern office, yet all the charm of a classic interior that feels as though it has been around for ages. The walls are painted @farrowandball #greensmoke and the ceiling is #pointing The French antique desk is from @langstonpimlico and the lighting by @vaughandesigns Photo by @chriswakefield.photography

This twin guest room in our coach house project is ready for holiday guests. What once was a derelict outbuilding, is now a warm and inviting guest house, packed full of charm. We used a fave print on the beds and cushions and paired it with a small scale, stripe and gingham to bring the room to life. Introducing rough boarding to the ceiling ensured we kept the character and warmth of the building. We hope everyone is enjoying their holidays! ❄️🤍

The cutest little loo in a recent project in Somerset. We used a fave small scale print wallpaper by @soanebritain and paired it with glazed pale pink wall tile from @firedearthuk We chose @farrowandball #slippersatin for the t&g panelling and love this combined with the marble floor tile… the sweetest hand painted birdy plates love their home over the loo. 🐥💕

We love a well stocked bar. Perfect for New Year’s Day! My mantra is that any surface in your home has the potential to be a bar. We love incorporating drinks trolleys into our interiors. Whether they’re new or vintage, rattan or brass, they’re always a yes! Alternatively, all you need is a great tray… fill it with the essentials and you’re ready to go. I love how inviting a bar feels and any corner is ready to serve! We hope everyone is enjoying their holidays and cheers to 2023 🥂🥃🍋

Introducing our latest project, the brand new show home at the @holburneparkbath development in Bath. The goal was to give each room within the home it’s own identity. We had so much fun playing with colour and pattern in each space to create layered interiors packed full of joy. A feast for the eyes, we wanted potential buyers to linger, rather than walk through quickly. Anything but the typical “show home look” which is most definitely not in our vocabulary. The walls are painted in @edwardbulmerpaint #teagreen and we love it as the backdrop for all the pretty prints and fabrics. 💚💕 Stay tuned for more pics of this project. Go check it out in person… or better yet, buy it 😉

A corner of the snug in our @holburneparkbath show home project. The aim was to bring a sense of heritage and character to this new-build property. We wanted the snug to be darker and moodier than the rest and have it’s own identity. The type of room you retire to in the evening with a great 🥃🍸. We brought in eclectic elements ranging from antique furniture and art to canary yellow velvet armchairs…It’s all about the mix. A Georgian mahogany desk acts as the perfect spot for a bar. A pair of lamps, a great tray and a joyful oil is all you need to make the corner pop. The walls and woodwork are painted in @farrowandball #redearth and we love the warmth and classicism it provides. Photo by @chriswakefield.photography 🤎💙🐆

Sunday morning means time for R&R. What better place to have a lie in than in this recently completed guest bedroom in Somerset. The prettiest prints by @penny_morrison_ltd set the tone for this cosy space. I hope everyone is enjoying their Sunday! 💕💕

A primary bedroom installed just before Christmas. We were so inspired by this bold @schumacher_uk chintz and decided to pull all the colours out of this hero print. We used it on the headboard and cushions and love it paired with smaller geometrics and ditsy floral prints. The walls are painted in @edwardbulmerpaint #lilacpink paired with the cutest scalloped #peagreen bedside tables. The perfect backdrop to the scheme. 💕💚 photo by @chriswakefield.photography

We love a little before and after moment. As you can see when we first entered this new-build property it was a true blank canvas. We weren’t able to change anything structural, so we opted to go bold with colour and pattern in order to make an impact. The snug is located on the first floor of the home and the aim was to make it a cosy sitting room reminiscent of an English club… a jewel box in contrast to the fresh and airy interiors of the surrounding rooms. We used @farrowandball #redearth on the walls and a fave @gpjbaker paisley print as the hero! We had so much fun collecting antiques to bring a sense of provenance into the room. A nod to Georgian Bath location. What do you guys think of this transformation? 💙🧡🧡🐆🐆

Happy Saturday! 💚💚 We love a layered vignette. This one is the corner of a recently completed drawing room. A bit of antique/vintage, a bit of new and a lot of fun! We layered these old oils (sourced from various markets) with a painted console we picked up online. All set on our fave @edwardbulmerpaint #granitegreen walls. Striking the right balance of hip and fun with tradition is what we’re all about. Photo by @chriswakefield.photography

Monday means back to work! We hope everyone is surviving the January blues. A chic little home office/ guest room makes the transition back to work after the holidays a bit more bearable. We designed this study to incorporate a bespoke trundle daybed which we had slipcovered in a denim blue gingham. The perfect bed for overflow guests, which also acts as a place to read and perch in what functions day-to-day as the #WFH hub. An antique oil painting I picked up in Paris depicts a French peasant lady and I just adore the colours in it. We had her framed in a contemporary box frame painted in @farrowandball #slippersatin which we just love set against the @edwardbulmerpaint #etruscanbrown walls. The blinds and cushions are in a pretty floral embroidery I brought back from a recent trip to Isreal. I loved the colours in it and used it to build the entire scheme. The cosiest space to work and slumber. 🤎🤎

A cosy corner from a recently installed primary bedroom. The classic bubble armchair by @sachalakic looks divine upholstered in a cosy boucle and surrounded by one of our fave @christopherfarrcloth prints … the perfect spot to open a good book. 🤍🤍

View into the utility room from the kitchen in our Holburne Park project. This space is totally helping us fight the winter blues…making us hopeful for spring. We used a fave @gpjbaker print on the walls in the utility and decided to carry it through onto the slipcovered bench in the kitchen. The scheme is full of fresh greens and pinks which cheer us up in any season. The dining chairs are vintage and we had them sprayed in @farrowandball #calkegreen with a cute squiggly print on the seat by @colefaxandfowler We love the pairing of vintage art and pretty prints with a classic marble tulip table. As you know we’re all about the mix 🤍🌿🌼💕

When our client purchased this Georgian townhouse in Cheltenham it was in a shocking state. After being an HMO for years, we had our work cut out for us transforming it back to its former glory of a single family home. The drawing room was painstakingly restored to showcase the home’s period features and impressive proportions. It’s so fun to reflect back on the hat it looked like when we first entered the property 🤍🤍

Happy Sunday! We hope everyone was able to get some well deserved R&R this weekend. We love this corner of a recently completed bedroom. A plethora of little prints and punchy colour make us so happy. Relaxed, yet energising… what we’re all about. I have recently discovered the most divine Italian ceramic homewares company. They kindly sent me some of their fab pieces and we were able to easily work them into our schemes. I love the glaze, weight and quality to their work. The ‘Pinecone’ collection is our fave with the most divine texture and variety of colours. If you want a bit of Italy in your home, Follow the instructions below to win stunning ceramic vases like the ones featured above. (Seen here in green and pink glaze)

Good morning! We decided to post a little mid-week pick-me-up featuring a scalloped console, a giant 🐚 and a plethora of ferns…all set in front of the prettiest green and gilt French antique Trumeau mirror. What’s not to love? 🧡🌿🌿

We are delighted to have our Cheltenham project featured in the February issue of @25beautifulhomesmagazine on newsstands now. Read about how we worked closely with our clients to restore their gorgeous Montpellier townhouse from a former HMO property to a liveable and elegant family home packed full of vintage and antiques… such a fun project to reflect on 🤍🤍

A fresh and fun twin room we just installed at @holburneparkbath ❤️💙blue and red is a classic colour combo. We used a fave navy ticking stripe everywhere and paired it with red accents. Antique 🦆🦆prints were given a new lease on life with navy bobbin frames. Red and blue, ticking and gingham…what’s not to love?

We are delighted to have our Somerset project featured in the March issue of @englishhomemag on newsstands now. Double happy to have our fave @alicepalmerco on the cover…hope you enjoy reading about how we helped make this Georgian beauty a home for the loveliest of clients. 🌿🌿🤍💚Special thanks to @rachelleedham for the fab feature

Happy Friday! We love a pretty utility room. In this space, we decided to skirt the washing machine and dryer to add warmth to the room and disguise the appliances. This is also a good solution for rooms where you do not want to change any joinery or fixed elements. Being a new build, we needed to work with the existing cabinetry, but add character and make it feel unique. This room also acts as an overflow for food storage and prep space as it is directly off of the kitchen. With direct access to the garden, we wanted a nod to the outdoors with space for flower arranging and potting. 🪴🪴🌸🌼

One of our most colourful and joyful sitting rooms to-date. We are thrilled to have our Brook Green Townhouse project featured in the March issue of @25beautifulhomesmagazine on newsstands now. Pick up your copy to see the rest of this joyous home…featuring this jewel box of a sitting room 💛💜💚

Another shot of our fave twin room in the recently completed Holburne Park project. We designed and had these scalloped headboards made for a bit of fun. We love them upholstered in a navy stripe with red piping. Antique duck prints are framed in navy bobbin frames, which give them a contemporary edge. An antique chest, red glossy lamp and gingham bedspreads, make for a for a bedroom gleaming with joy. 🦆❤️💙

Corner of the sitting room in our Camden Apartment project. Our client was a young single gal and she wanted her home to reflect her personality. We had so much fun playing with colour and pattern in this space to make it feel cosy and packed full of joy. Perfect for a sunny day like today. The walls are painted in @farrowandball #pointing and a bespoke candy pink gloss bobbin mirror sits above the watermelon velvet sofa. Playful prints and earthy textures… what more could we want? 💕💕

A corner of a bedroom from our recent coach house conversion project. Formerly an outbuilding, we worked closely with our clients to transform the building into the perfect guesthouse on their property. We used so many lovely prints and textures to keep the space feeling fresh and cosy. We cladded the ceiling in a rough boarding as a nod to the building’s former use and to add texture and warmth to the space. The original thick walls of the structure allowed us the opportunity to incorporate a window seat, providing the perfect place for guests to read and relax. Photo by @chriswakefield.photography 💕🤍

Scallops, frills and chintz galore. We had so much with this primary bedroom scheme. Fresh pinks and greens play well together with some of our fave prints. The perfect way to add soul to a new-build property. Walls are painted in @edwardbulmerpaint #lilacpink and the bedside tables are #peagreen hero print is #cranleygarden by @schumacher_uk 💕💕💚

A little bedside moment from our Somerset project. We used a fave @soanebritain fabric on the headboard and paired it with the prettiest @lewisandwood print on both walls and cushions. Bespoke scalloped bedside tables by @sarahvanrenen look fab paired with the prettiest blue lamps by @vaughandesigns A fresh and pretty scheme all set within the most divine Georgian house 🌿🌸

Penelope being her usual cute self around this breakfast area set-up. We love a mix of eras…from vintage to modern, this space feels timeless, chic and fun. We bought the French still life oil at market and love the soft greens and punchy yellows. It totally helped drive the scheme. Vintage Chinese chippendale chairs painted in @farrowandball #calkegreen look fun around a classic tulip table, paired with a slipcovered bench in a pretty block printed cotton by @gpjbaker 🌿💕🌼 We can’t help but feel energised and excited for spring. Anyone else?

All about the details. We love a blue and white scheme 💙🤍…we did just that in a project in London. Fun prints and fresh blueish greens make for a super chic home office  day-to-day and guest bedroom on occasion. We used @farrowandball light blue on the walls and a fave @romo_fabrics velvet on the sofa paired with fun prints as accents.

A little before and after moment from the study in our Camden project. When we first took on this project this room was dreary and tired. It was at the back of the property where the light wasn’t amazing. We decided to go bold with colour, using @farrowandball #indiayellow on the walls and a fun RAL cranberry in the scalloped shelves. A big piece of art from @studio.ham takes centre stage paired with eclectic furniture and printed fabrics. Truly a joyful space to work and enjoy. 💛🐫🌴

View into the twin room from the kitchenette in our coach house project. We love the prettiness of this scheme, set in the most gorgeous 18th century outbuilding, nestled within the English countryside... it’s so picturesque. We kept it fresh and sweet with a fave @penny_morrison_ltd print on the beds and soft creams and blues taking centre stage. It’s warm and inviting for guests of all ages. 🤍🤍🌿
Reflecting on a fresh blue and white scheme from a project in Oxford as we look forward to spring. 🤍💙🌿 The most classic colour palette and a go-to favourite of ours. Anyone else?

We love a little pink bedroom moment. We used a couple of our fave @penny_morrison_ltd prints for the groundwork of this scheme. The prettiest guest bedroom in the outbuilding of a larger home. The project was a complete refurbishment of a dilapidated 18th century coach house with the aim to turn it into a refuge for guests and family. 💕💕🌿

Styling is a large part of our job. We love curating layered and individual vignettes throughout all of our interiors. The key is scale and proportion. Something from nature, something glossy and something with texture. It is important to play with heights and proportions in order to create visual interest. The perfectly imperfect look is what we’re always after. This is from a recent install at our Chelsea studio project. A fave @slimaaronsofficial on the wall (reflected in the mirror) dictated the palette and overall look…fresh and fun 🌿💕🤍

Pink to make the boys wink 😉 💕 In compact bathrooms and small spaces, we think the best approach is to clad the entire room in one material. We chose this Rosalina honed marble tile by @mandarinstoneofficial and used it on every surface. Floors and walls are covered in this soft pink stone and we love it combined with the brass accents. It’s playful and young, yet sophisticated. Fun fact, the mirror opens with storage behind it… making use of every inch. What do we think?

We are delighted to have our Tetbury project featured in the April issue of @period_living magazine. Special thanks to @alisongibbstylingandwriting for putting together this lovely piece. Reflecting on these photos makes us very excited for the spring. 🌿💕💚

We love a fully upholstered wall… inset reading lights provide practicality and we love them installed on the upholstered panels. We used a fave bold chintz as wall panelling, cushions and blinds in the room. In this instance, the bed floats in the middle of this small studio apartment. Because of this, the headboard has to act as I divide within the space. Go bold or go home is always our motto 🌸💚💕

Spring is in the air…🌷🌸 A view into a little girl’s room from a recent project in London. It was the smallest bedroom in the house, so we decided to build a daybed in the window with deep drawers for storage. A pretty mural wallpaper covers the walls and creates a sense of whimsy. One of our fave spaces for one of our youngest clients 💕💕

View into the kitchen in a project in Somerset. We love this soft and pretty scheme with @farrowandball #lichen on the island and #jameswhite on the cupboards. Pale greens and soft creams brighten up this space. Our clients inherited a virtually brand new kitchen when they purchased the house. Unfortunately, it didn’t function appropriately for their needs. We adapted it to maximise storage and practically, incorporating an integrated wine fridge, low level lighting and a plethora of storage. We were so pleased we were able to adapt what was there to serve their needs. Kitchens are one of our fave spaces to design. 🥬🌿🤍

Corner of a dressing room in a project in Bath. We love a print on print moment. We used a small scale print on the walls and the tiniest geometric print on the chair. We love it paired with a punchy chintz on the blinds and cushion. @farrowandball #templetonpink is the perfect pairing to the paper. 💕💚
A little nod to St.Patrick’s Day ☘️☘️ with this  loo from a recent project in Somerset. Fresh and pretty in green. Wishing everyone a fab upcoming weekend filled with the luck of the Irish. ☘️💚

Corner of a bedroom from a project in London. A cotton velvet is always a yes and this deep olive version is no exception. We used it on a bespoke bench and headboard, piped in the palest of pinks. The walls are #farrowandballfrenchgrey and bespoke bedside tables are sprayed in #farrowandballsettingplaster full-gloss… All derived from a fave @christopherfarrcloth print which we used as curtains and cushions in the scheme. Cosy and inviting is the ultimate goal 🤍💕🤍

View into the bedroom from the hall in our Coach House project. We decided to clad the ceiling in rough boarding in order to bring texture and character into this 18th century outbuilding. A limed oak floor and clean plaster walls are the perfect compliment to the pops of colour and pretty fabrics. We did the joinery in #farrowandballlightblue with the cutest striped fabric panels to add warmth. We love a good view through a doorway. 🤍

View into the front entry from the sitting room in our @holburneparkbath showhome project. We layered antiques and eclectic pieces into the room to add warmth and interest. @edwardbulmerpaint #granitegreen lifts the scheme and acts as the perfect backdrop to the furnishings. An antique French Trumeau mirror looks pretty paired with a bespoke scalloped console painted in #brickedwardbulmer We’re all about the mix. 💚💚

Spring is in the air! 🌼🌿Flashback to a fave twin room we installed last year. Yellow gingham, fresh greens and the prettiest floral embroidery combine to create the cutest guest bedroom scheme in our Tetbury project. Is anyone else looking forward to the warmer weather? ☀️🌼💚

We love a front entry hall vignette. We sourced these pretty hand painted birdy plates from @vinterior and love them displayed around the mirror. A bespoke painted Gustavian sideboard painted in @farrowandball #frenchgrey acts as the perfect spot for storage and display. A huge waft of Cow Parsley, antique accessories and a pair of pretty lamps by @vaughandesigns make us swoon. 🌿🤍

Corner of a studio apartment we recently completed in Chelsea. We chose this compact @swyft_home sofa as it was the only piece we could source that would come apart into enough pieces to fit into this small space. It looks fab in this mossy green velvet which works perfectly with our scheme. Bright pinks and greens look great paired with vintage elements such as the midcentury rattan drinks trolley and the massive @slimaaronsofficial print which adds the ‘wow’ factor we so needed. Walls are @farrowandball #wimbournewhite 💕🌸💙

A rare, more neutral palette shown here in the drawing room of our Cheltenham project. We used @farrowandball #schoolhousewhite on the walls paired with #hardwickwhite on the woodwork and #downpipe on the windows. The aim was for the architecture to take centre stage, creating a calm and timeless scheme. 🌿🤍🖤

Corner of a sitting room in a project in London. The brief was to create a cosy and eclectic interior that would work for a young single gal. She wanted it to reflect her personality, and feel like a personal refuge in the middle of the city. We found this midcentury armchair on @ebay had it sprayed in a fab emerald green and upholstered it in a fave leopard by @colefaxandfowler 💚🐆We love it’s clean lines paired with the ditsy fabric of the cushion by @schumacher_uk The existing chimney breast was without a fireplace. For this reason, we bought a French mantelpiece from a reclamation yard, painted the inside in black and filled it with candles. This creates the atmosphere of a fireplace, without the hassle of actually installing one. Layered, eclectic and cosy is what we’re all about. 💕

Swipe for a before and after situation… we love designing boutique office spaces. This is one we did for a small estate agency. It was incredible to see it transform from a drab and uninspiring building to an inviting and individual space. We used the existing alcove to build in a drinks cabinet with integrated fridge and coffee station. We wanted the space to be more flexible and be suitable for all different types of working. We hope everyone is enjoying their last day at the office before the well needed long weekend! ❤️💙🤎

We love a transformation. 🧡🌿 Our client didn’t want to completely overhaul this kitchen as it is her holiday home. For this reason, we decided to rethink the colour and introduce a built-in bench for optimal seating. One of the first things we did was remove the outdated splash back tile and install t&g boarding. We love how classic and timeless it feels. Painting the kitchen this warm terracotta was a bold move, but we love how cheery and inviting it feels, especially paired with olive greens and the punchy floral prints of the cushions. So much fun looking back on a project’s journey! 💚🧡🐆🌿

Spring has sprung! Another shot of our fave Primary Bedroom from an install last year. It is definitely giving us all of the seasonal feels 🌸🌷🌿We had so much fun layering this interior with pretty prints and fresh tones. The rug is a fave from @penny_morrison_ltd and we love it paired with the flouncy @gpjbaker upholstered chairs. The walls are @edwardbulmerpaint #lilacpink which is the perfect neutral backdrop to the scheme. @colefaxandfowler curtains and a bold chintz by @schumacher_uk come together to serve botanical goals 💚🌸🌿

Details from a recent bathroom install. We love using wallpaper in bathrooms. It adds such warmth and really pulls the scheme together we paired this pretty print with blinds made up in a waxed linen by @schumacher_uk with a fave @samuelandsons trim. 🤍🤍

A fave guest bedroom from our recent coach house project. We used a punchy print on the headboards, valances and cushions and paired it with checks, stripes and a ditsy block floral on the chair. The scheme is one of our faves… calm and soothing, yet fun and youthful.

Spring has sprung! We are so feeling the brighter tones and cheery prints as we move into the warmer weather. A few details from a recent install in Chelsea. We mixed a neutral animal print on the chairs with a bold and vibrant chintz on the blinds, headboard and cushions to create a jewel box of a studio flat… perfect for weekends away or quick work trips. 🌸🌿💗

A fun view down the stairs at a project in Camden. We love how the red candy stripe runner guides you through this vertical apartment… linking each floor. We paired it with a fave @clarencehousetextiles print on the blinds and neutral @farrowandball #pointing walls. We really are all about that pop ❤️

Pretty dressing room from our @holburneparkbath show home project. We used a fave little print @gpjbaker wallpaper on the walls and paired it with @farrowandball #templetonpink on the woodwork. Being a new build property, we really wanted to bring in the character by incorporating varying prints, flouncy fabrics and eclectic furniture. The perfect spot to get ready in the morning. 💚💕

location.city_name: London Borough of Hammersmith and Fulham

social_posts.post_text: Breakfast area in a kitchen in London. We designed this curved banquette in a yellow leather for a pop of colour and to provide ample seating for the whole family. We love how it instantly became the hub of the home. The deep aubergine on the island pairs perfectly with greens, blues and of course the HIT of yellow 🍋💜💙

Detail shot from a recent bathroom design. We love this cheery wallpaper by @gpjbaker It is getting us so in the mood for the warmer weather. We paired it with the cutest Swedish blind for privacy and flounce, as well as our fave tone by @edwardbulmerpaint #aquatic on the panelling. 🐦💛💙 Who’s excited to see the rest of this space?

A little Sunday R&R… we designed this bathroom in Chelsea with a fave pink marble tile as the groundwork. Switching it up between mosaic and large format, makes this space feel luxurious and considered. By sticking to one material on all the walls, the room feels instantly larger. Brass and pink, what’s not to love? 💕✨

Corner of a sitting room from a recent project in Bath. We used @farrowandball #redearth on the walls and paired it with a plethora of fun prints and colours. We wanted the space to feel cosy and inviting, yet joyous and fun!🧡🌿🦜💙💛

A corner of our recent Chelsea Studio project. Styling is a key part of our job. We love a layered vignette. It’s all about scale, colour and balance. Something glossy, something patterned and something organic. It’s all about the mix 💛💕🌿

So thrilled that it is officially alfresco dining season. 🌿💙🍴We had so much fun designing this exterior dining space last year. One of our fave @christopherfarrcloth prints takes centre stage. We used it on the bespoke banquette and love how vibrant and inviting it feels. Table by @fermob photo by @chriswakefield.photography

We are happy to announce that due to a number of recent project wins we are looking for an amazing person to join our growing team. The ideal candidate is located in the Bath area with experience in residential interior design. We are an extremely fast paced and fun team working on a number of projects in the UK and Europe. We need a highly organised person who is keen to work on varying projects at all stages of the design process. Knowledge of AutoCad, Photoshop, Indesign and Excel is a plus, but above all else, a positive attitude with a passion for design is a must! Please send a DM or an email to studio@seansymingtondesign.com with you CV to apply!

A little Sunday morning kitchen inspo from our Camden Apartment project. We love going deep and moody in compact spaces. We opted to paint the existing floorboards in a checkerboard pattern using @farrowandball Mahogany and School House White. Removing the cupboards under the sink allowed us to introduce the warmth of a flouncy skirt with coordinated blinds. Shelves filled with pretty and practical ceramics as well as a warm terracotta on the walls (@edwardbulmerpaint Sang de Boeuf) create this jewel box of a city kitchen. Swipe to see the before images. 🤎🌿🍐
Some of our favourite bedside moments… We love layered, cosy bedrooms which evoke a sense of calm and relaxation, but aren’t short on personality. Which one of these is your fave?

The process of how we transformed this builder-basic utility room and breakfast area into something fun and inviting simply by introducing pretty wallpaper, printed fabrics and a plethora of colour. It’s fun to look back on the blank canvas we started with. The perfect scheme for a sunny summer day. 💕🥬🍋

A fresh and summery loft bedroom from a recent project in the Cotswolds. We love mixing and matching prints… if you look closely the walls are papered in a ditsy seaweed print by @colefaxandfowler Pops of colour and eclectic furniture come together to create the perfectly layered interior. Great inspo for a hot summer’s day. 💕🌿

Some of our fave shots of a super colourful and super lux drawing room from a project in London. 💜💚💙 One of our fave projects to-date. The clients allowed us to go bold and have fun with colour. We wanted it to feel like a jewel box at the front of the house. It needed to be formal enough for entertaining, yet casual enough for everyday family life. We chose these supremely comfortable aubergine sofas from @boconceptuk and paired them with a bespoke mustard velvet ottoman that we drew in studio and had made. A mix of furniture eras make it collected and fun. The walls are @farrowandball #inchyrablue and I love it holds the room. What do we think?

Some of our favourite reading corners from past projects. From contemporary to classic, we love designing spaces that are ideal for cosying up and reading a great book. When possible, we like to incorporate a chair into the corner of a bedroom or hallway. Not only does it instantly make a space feel more luxurious, but it also feels inviting and warm. Which one of these spots would be your fave choice for a 🍷📖?

Good morning from Penny dog! Happy Monday. 🌤️ We love the English light in the morning during the summer. The days feel so long and glorious, what a difference sun makes. The kitchen dining area in our @holburneparkbath showhome project. View into the utility room through the door. Fresh greens and pinks are always a yes. Hope everyone has a fab week ahead! 🍋🥬💕

This entrance in a project in Camden was a challenging space to design as it was so long and narrow and had a massive radiator on one wall. We opted to paint the entire space white and smother the walls in prints of flora and fauna. We concealed the radiator with a skirted and scalloped console which adds warmth and makes the hall feel furnished. Dividing the space with a candy stripe curtain visually breaks it up and creates a sort of vestibule by the front door. One of our fave spaces to-date! 🤍❤️🌿

Fun detail shots from a glamorous bedroom install from a couple of years back. The brief was to create something layered with pretty florals and accents of charcoal with pink. We love the glamour of the @slim_aarons photograph of @joancollinsdbe with her poodle in an all pink interior… Layering pretty prints… from leopard to chintz, we’re all about the contrast 🤍💕🐩

Another sunny day ahead of us, so we felt it fitting to show a bright and light sitting room from last year. We love using foliage from the garden to create drama and add whimsy to the indoors. Dressing a mantel in any season completely changes the feeling of a room. Soft yellows and pale greens create the feeling of freshness and warmth in this sitting room. One of our all-time faves! 🌿🌼 We have a couple of exciting photoshoots coming up and we can’t wait to show you what we’re working on at the moment.
A little bedside moment in the Cotswolds… A combination of pretty block prints and antiques come together to create an eclectic and inviting bedroom scheme. 🌿💙

Pick up the August issue of @homebeautiful magazine to read the wonderful feature on our Camden Apartment project. Thank you to @brittanysmith_writing for this fab piece. We are so excited to be featured across the pond in Australia. On newsstands now! 💕💕

A little kitchenette from a guesthouse we designed in Somerset. A guest kitchen is a great feature to incorporate when possible as it means guests and family can cater to themselves without feeling like they’re imposing. In this instance, the hallway connecting the two bedrooms had just enough space for a small fridge, sink and breakfast larder, perfectly equipped with everything needed for a quick snack or cup of tea. We used t&g panelling on the walls and added a marble shelf for essential crockery. A tall cupboard conceals the appliances such as the microwave, coffee maker and kettle. We used @farrowandball Old White on the cupboards and love how fresh it feels with the nickel hardware. ☕️🫖🥐

Introducing our latest project. A contemporary family home in London. We had so much fun infusing every room with colour and pattern. Luckily, our clients weren’t afraid to go bold and I think it totally paid off. This breakfast area is next to the large open kitchen and is perfect for family gatherings. Stay tuned to see the rest of the spaces from this project! 🐵❤️🌿 photo by @chriswakefield.photography

A little bedside moment from a recent project in London. We used one of our fave colours @edwardbulmerpaint #granitegreen on the walls to create a soothing and calm atmosphere for this bedroom. Soft watermelon and greens come together to create a pretty and layered scheme, perfect for a restful weekend! 🐅🌴💕

A little house tour…. Some of our fave shots from a project in Cheltenham. We loved mixing vintage and new to create a layered and dramatic interior. The client wanted a monochromatic scheme of greys, charcoals and earth tones. We used #schoolhousewhite on the walls with #hardwickwhite on the woodwork and stairs 🖤🌿 a collection of antique hat stands work so well on the front hall table, we love mixing eclectic pieces to create character and visual interest in our interiors.
We love a matchy-matchy moment. We used a fave punchy print ‘Balangan’ by @manuelcanovasparis on the walls and as the blind, creating a jewel box effect… perfectly joyful for this craft room. 🧡💜

A little indoor-outdoor dining moment. When we designed this kitchen, we wanted to ensure that there was enough space for large gathering. We installed a 3 metre long bespoke banquette which allowed for ample comfortable seating. Our clients aren’t afraid of colour, so we took the opportunity to play with pretty fabrics and varying prints in cushions and upholstery. A gallery wall of favoured memorabilia and art was a fun experiment in colour and custom framing. We love the mix of the inherited dining chairs with the contemporary oak dining table by @konkfurniture 🌿💛💚❤️

Corner of a bedroom from a recent project in London. We chose a pretty @colefaxandfowler wallpaper and had it installed above and below the picture rail in order to make the room feel taller and more hip. Soft greens, pale blues and a punchy headboard make us happy! Hope everyone is enjoying their Sunday. ☕️💤🌿

Another angle of the breakfast area in a recent project in west London. We love the pop of coral in this contemporary kitchen. We had the chairs made to feel cosy and comfortable and love them paired with the clean lines of the classic tulip table. This table isn’t the only area for dining within the home, but in fact acts as more of a social space for family game night and an impromptu book 📖We love incorporating various types of seating into our interiors to inspire different activities and uses. ❤️❤️ photo by @chriswakefield.photography

I hope everyone is enjoying this sunny Saturday morning. We thought we would feature another angle of a recent guest bedroom install. We love incorporating seating areas into bedrooms as it allows for a great place for reading and relaxing, giving the room more purpose and functionality. This room is primarily used by the parents and in-laws of our client so we wanted it to feel inviting and warm for their stays in London. We used a pretty seaweed motif wallpaper and paired it with a fave green by @edwardbulmerpaint on the woodwork. We wanted it to feel colourful, yet calming. What do you guys think of this space? 🌿💕🐦

A little before-during-after moment. When we first met with our clients their kitchen was a huge open concept space. We knew instantly that we wanted to make use of the massive wall opposite the kitchen island by incorporating a built-in banquette, which would maximise seating and bring in warmth. We drew and designed this space taking into consideration our client’s art and seating requirements. It was a really big exercise in colour, print and lighting. Believe it or not, it took a lot of planning to achieve this effortless, eclectic look. 😅 The outcome is a joyful dining area that has become the hub of the home. 🌿🍽️💛💙

Happy Tuesday! We decided to post a photo of the snug from our most recent project, a Georgian Manor House in Gloucestershire. We wanted this room to feel inviting and casual, perfect for family game and movie night. This is the space that gets used the most by the children and the beloved family dog. For this reason, durability and practicality was at the forefront of the design. We used a @ruggable rug and a slipcovered sofa which can be both be thrown in the wash and easily cleaned. The room is cosy and inviting, yet in keeping with the rest of the house. We were thrilled when we found a large collection of antique hunting prints at @jmrantiques which fit perfectly above the L-shaped sofa. The palette is neutral and calm and these work so well with the scheme. Who’s excited to see more spaces we designed in this lovely home? 🐶🤍

We’re all about making an entrance. Our Georgian Manor House project has the most divine hallway and staircase. We love the scale and drama of this room. By adding panelling the space feels grander and better proportioned. We opted to carry it up the stairs and painted it in a fave @farrowandball neutral #slippersatin with #bluegrey above. The aim was for the space to feel timeless and “unrenovated” yet, fresh and current. Herringbone floors and chunky sisal carpeting set the tone for inherited brown furniture, which hopefully have new life in this home. 🌿🤍🤍

Corner of a dressing room from a recent project in London. We used our fave #tigerpalm print everywhere and love it paired with the punchy coral tone of #fruitfool by @farrowandball on the joinery. The cutest spot to get ready in the morning 🐅🌴💕

When possible, we love incorporating desks into rooms. They provide another function to a space and are even better when antique. This Georgian bureau was a great option as it looks equally beautiful when closed. Any chance to add extra storage to a room is a yes in our book… plus we’re a fan of brown furniture. Who’s excited to see the rest of this recently completed Georgian drawing room? 📖🤎🌿

We hope everyone is looking forward to the weekend ahead, with some needed R&R. We love going bold in guest bedrooms. This guest suite in London was so much fun to design using rich blues and vibrant greens. The dressing table acts as the perfect bedside moment. We love mixing and matching bedside tables. In this room we used a brown chest of drawers on one side of the bed with this vintage rattan desk on the other side… the perfect eclectic combo. 💚💙

Dressing a hall is one of our fave things to do. We found this fab country house sideboard at a market and knew instantly it was the perfect piece because of it’s character and proportion. Layering in a bit of vintage and new as well as fresh cut flowers from the garden, this hallway vignette feels inviting and warm.🌿🧺🤍🤎photo by @chriswakefield.photography

Two views of an ultra luxurious and super chic maximalist drawing room in the works for a fabulous client in London. We are so excited to install this space. A double sided sofa, leopard, upholstered walls and fringe galore. What’s not to love? We adore seeing our designs come to life in render by the talented @tiiukardi 🐆💚🌿🧡🐅

A sun filled and bright sitting room from a recent project in Gloucestershire. We used pale blues and creams to create a fresh take on English country style. We wanted the room to feel light and airy and like it had been around for years. We sourced the bergere chairs at auction and had them upholstered in a wide stripe by @schumacher_uk we love the contemporary edge it gives them. Creating a seating area in a window is always a yes. The perfect area for entertaining. A collection of blue and white gives the room character and provenance. They add to the layered look we so love. 🌿🤍 The walls are painted in a fave neutral #shadedwhite with #slippersatin on the woodwork. Both by @farrowandball The new mantel was made bespoke in a Bath stone to feel like it had been original to the house. Photography by @chriswakefield.photography

A little secret door moment from a project in London. When we first met our clients this space had no obvious wall for the bed to be situated. The room is located in the eaves of the property and therefore all the walls were pitched and angled. We chose to divide the room by installing a partition which gave a solid wall for the headboard. By incorporating a jib door, the symmetry of the room wasn’t thrown off. The new room behind the bed is perfect for backup storage and suitcases. Walls are painted in #granitegreen by @edwardbulmerpaint with @farrowandball #allwhite on the woodwork. 🚪💚🐅🌴💕

View into the hall from the sitting room of our Holburne Park show home project. We used @edwardbulmerpaint #granitegreen on the walls and love how fresh and vibrant it feels. The aim was to give this new-build property a feeling of character and tradition. We sourced the oil landscapes at an antique market and paired them with a vintage decorative console we found online. We love the layered look 🖼️🐚🌿 photo by @chriswakefield.photography

A cosy corner of the snug in our Gloucestershire Manor House project. We designed this break-fronted joinery to span the width of the room in order to house a plethora of toys, board games and various necessities. The top drawer slides out to become a desk, perfect for homework and studying after school. The joinery is painted in @farrowandball #denimes and we love how rich it feels, changing from day to night. 📚

An elegant staircase from a recent project in Gloucestershire. We used a fave sisal for the stair runner and rug in the main entry hall to add texture and warmth to the space. A herringbone timber floor and fresh white panelling adds a modern edge to this traditional interior. 🌿🤍🤎 photo by @chriswakefield.photography

Hope everyone is getting a little Sunday R&R. We love this punch colour combo for this recently completed guest bedroom in a project in London. A bamboo desk serves also as a bedside table on one side of the bed with a brown chest of drawers on the other side. We love to mix eras and styles of furniture within interiors. We found the Chinoiserie chandelier on eBay and had it sprayed navy for another fun pop. Photo by @chriswakefield.photography 💙💚💙

Penny dog enjoying the sunshine from the window in our bedroom in Bath. We had so much fun designing this room to be a cosy and warm refuge to retire to in the evening. The walls and woodwork are painted @farrowandball #redearth which creates a sort of cocooning effect. We had the half-tester and headboard made in a playful @schumacher1889 fabric and just love the combo paired with a spotty print by @gpjbaker The room is warm and inviting… one of my fave spots in the house 🐅🌴🐅 photo by @chriswakefield.photography

View into the study in a project in London. We used a @farrowandball #stiffkeyblue on the woodwork and joinery and paired it with a fun wallpaper by @schumacher_uk 🐎💙 Dark, moody and dramatic… perfect for WFH days.

Our tiny guest bedroom in Bath. We split the existing room in half to incorporate a new bathroom on the first floor and therefore ended up with a much smaller box bedroom. With smaller spaces, sometimes it’s fun to go dark. I love the matchy-matchy moment with @soanebritain #scrollingfern on the headboard, valance, chair and blind… cute and cosy ready for single guests 😉🌿💙

Henry relaxing in the gracious hallway at our project in Gloucestershire. We love the scale and proportion of this space. We used @farrowandball #bluegrey on the walls with #slippersatin on the panelling and woodwork. Inherited antiques combined with fresh blues and greens keep this space timeless and welcoming. 🌿🤍🐶

We hope everyone is looking forward to the  weekend ahead. This bespoke banquette we had made is perfect for entertaining and weekend dinner parties. Colour and pattern is always a yes as it adds energy and life to this family kitchen. We put together the gallery wall by framing our client’s existing art and memorabilia in various frames including colourful bobbin, painted bamboo and limed oak. This eclectic mix comes together to ensure the space feels joyful and personal. 🖼️❤️🍋🌿

A cosy corner of the sitting room in a project in Gloucestershire. We love that it is nearly fire season as the evenings are getting cooler… this room would be perfect for cuddling up in and enjoying a good book. Walls are painted in @farrowandball #shadedwhite with #slippersatin woodwork, complimented by pretty pastels in the fabrics. 🍷📚🤍🌿

Loving this WFH moment on this cosy autumnal morning. We designed bespoke joinery to wrap the room and opted to paint the entire space a dark moody blue. We love how this offsets the antiques and memorabilia. The aim was to create a fresh take on a traditional Georgian study. One of my fave rooms in our Gloucestershire Manor House project. 💙📚
Good morning from Henry on a Saturday in October that feels like a Saturday in August! We hope everyone has a wonderful and restful weekend 🐶⛅️🌿

The corner of our kitchen in Bath. I didn’t want this space to feel too heavy or “fitted” so instead I designed a pair of dresser units with classic pediments to flank the existing chimney breast. They are practical for both prep and storage. The bifold doors conceal the “clutter” when closed and display the marble worktops and deep cranberry t&g internals when open. Cabinets are painted in @farrowandball #settingplaster with #preferencered inside. I love this colour combo with the marble worktops and floors. 🥬💕👨‍🍳

How you see me, now you don’t. When we designed this snug joinery we knew we wanted to incorporate a spot for homework and studying. This concealed pull-out desk is the perfect spot for it. Joinery is painted in @farrowandball #denimes with the walls in #shadedwhite 🤍🤍📚

Just a casual “candid” 😉 shot of me in the studio… I love scheming up new designs and we are so blessed to have a sample library with thousands of fabrics and materials at our finger tips. This really helps make the design process more inspiring and exciting from concept to completion 🤍✍️

View from the sample room into the desk area of my office in Bath. The ceiling is vaulted and glass so I opted to tent the room in a fave @schumacher_uk fabric which is reminiscent of our company branding. I love the cosy yet soft feeling that working in a tented room provides. Blue and white is always a classic and it acts as sort of a neutral for us! The rest of the space is sisal carpeting and bright white walls, allowing us to scheme without distraction 🤍💙🤍🐆
Detail shot from a very glamorous and very fun dressing room. We love being adventurous with colour. Glossy emerald joinery paired with @gucci heron wallpaper… what’s not to love? 🦢💕💚

Some of our favourite single bed situations. Some are children’s rooms and some are guest rooms. We love designing bedrooms that work for all ages. A daybed is a great solution for small spaces and a pair of single beds is a fave option for both children and guests. Stay tuned as we have some fab twin rooms and daybed situations in the works now… installing soon 😉💕

Our fave part of the design process… putting schemes together. 🤍🤍It was so fun having @chriswakefield.photography in the studio to capture us hard at work. There’s truly never a dull moment around here 😜

Happy Sunday! We hope everyone is enjoying this fabulous autumnal morning. The perfect day for a lunch with friends and family. The kitchen is painted in @farrowandball #settingplaster with #preferencered in the interior. We chose to clad the ceiling in t&g paneling to add interest and character to the room. The existing Bath stone mantel provided the perfect location for the range. We designed the alcove units with bifold doors in order to accommodate a breakfast area on the left side and plenty of storage for glassware on the right. It’s a great space for cooking and entertaining. 🥕🥦🍠

A cosy corner of a recent snug install in Gloucestershire, perfect for autumnal mornings. We chose soft textured linens for the upholstery and layered them with subtle, neutral prints in the cushions and rug. The walls are painted in #shadedwhite with #slippersatin on the woodwork and ceiling. The outcome is a practical and stylish space that will stand the test of time. 🤍🤍

A little weekend inspiration. Throwing it back to one of my fave kitchens ever. Our Georgian Villa project is full of pale greens and fresh cream tones with @farrowandball #vertedeterre on the island and #jamesswhite on the cabinetry. We enjoyed designing this kitchen to maximise storage space and up the style factor. It is perfect for family cooking and entertaining. 🥬🥕🌿

A non-interior related shot this morning. People are always saying I need to post more photos of myself on IG, so here I am perusing my fave city. I never tire of strolling the streets of Venice at any season… even in the cold. 🇮🇹🍝🚤

Corner of our snug in Bath. We designed this joinery to go up and over the sofa creating a cosy library feeling to the space. It also allowed for swing arm reading lights to be installed for added functionality. This is really the room that gets used the most by everyone in the family 🐶👨🏼‍🤝‍👨🏽so it needed to be durable and practical. We love using this space in the evening for TV viewing or a good 📚Joinery is painted in @farrowandball #settingplaster with #preferencered internal.

Our kitchen at home in Bath. I wanted a space that was joyful yet practical. I didn’t want the kitchen to feel too “fitted” so I designed the island to be as open as possible allowing space for baskets and display. The existing chimney breast provided the perfect spot for the range and allowed for the introduction of two alcove units with elegant pediments either side. As counter space was limited, the large island is crucial for prep space and I love the sleekness that the large slab of marble provides. Everything on display gets used on a regular basis and it really is a working kitchen. 🥬🧺💕

Scheming is a large part of the design process. We love putting together layered and individual designs that are unique to each client. Our pinboard in the office is constantly evolving and ever changing, as we develop the design...📍💕🌿

Our Sitting Room in Bath. I wanted this room to feel cosy and vibrant. To achieve this, I decided to cover the walls in a teal grasscloth and had the woodwork painted into the paper. The outcome is a sort of ‘jewel-box’ effect. I love how warm and welcoming it feels. We enjoy sitting by the fire in the evening with a glass of 🍷. It’s such a great room for the long English winters. Woodwork is painted in an archive colour called #sugarbaglight by @farrowandball with @phillipjeffriesltd #bermudahemp grasscloth and #pointing on the ceiling. Photo by @chriswakefield.photography

We hope everyone is enjoying a little Sunday R&R. This is a shot of my top floor guest bedroom. It’s cosy and warm… a great spot to snuggle up. We built storage in the eaves concealed by built-in bookcases which are so practical and add to the cosiness. Walls are painted in @edwardbulmerpaint #lilacpink and we love it paired with the texture of the sisal. A fun silk fringe around the headboard adds a touch of glam to the room. 💕

A cosy seating area in the large window of our Gloucestershire Manor House project. We wanted the space to feel light and bright… in order to achieve this, we opted for pale blues and fresh creams combined with #shadedwhitefarrowandball on the walls and #slippersatinfarrowandball on the woodwork. Fresh foliage from the garden helps bring the outdoors in. 🌿🌿 We found the vintage French armchairs online and had them upholstered in a wide graphic stripe by @schumacher_uk we love the modern edge it adds to the room. Light, bright and elegant. 🤍🌿

Corner of our sitting room in Bath with the sunlight flooding in. I love how warm and inviting this room is at any season. The vibrant grasscloth adds so much texture and glamour to the space. We had a custom bobbin fender made and painted it in @edwardbulmerpaint #pompadour … the perfect raspberry pink. It is the perfect spot to sit during cosy nights by the fire. 💕💙

We are busy decking the halls over here! 🎄🌟 I know it is customary to wait until December 1st (at least) But with everything going on in the world, I decided we needed a little bit of joy and sparkle in our lives to lift our spirits. I love filling our tree with little critters. From polar bears wearing cable-knit vests to mice on skis, I have collected little felt animals for years. Stay tuned to see how we have packed our home full of holiday cheer! I am so looking forward to sharing the finished rooms with you all. I hope it brings you as much joy as it does us. Special thanks to my team who have helped me put it all together this year… we all know it takes a village. 😂😉Has anyone else started decorating yet?

A shot of my staircase in Bath. I absolutely love layered and luscious garlands. This one is a combination of real and faux foliage and is crammed full of everything from dried hydrangeas and fruit to pheasants and feathers. I love decorating with natural elements and more is always more. I much prefer the cosiness of this than the “glitz” of too many plastic baubles. We decided to hang velvet ribbon casually from the bottom and avoided bows. I love how whimsical and casual it feels. The combination of fruit such as clementines and pomegranates are a homage to tradition. It is truly an instant mood booster every morning.

Happy Thanksgiving to our American followers. 🦃🍁🍂I thought I would throw it back to this autumnal kitchen from a project in London. I hope everyone who is celebrating enjoys their weekend and has a blast entertaining in their spaces.

More is more and less is a bore when it comes to Christmas. We had so much fun decking the halls this year, bringing in holiday magic to our cosy home. I love using elements from nature such as foliage and hydrangeas combined with vibrant velvet ribbons and fruits. The mantel is the perfect place to go bold and make a statement. The more time you spend in the space, the more details you notice. From the perching pheasants on top of the tree to the quails nesting on the mantle, the room feels so cosy and inviting, perfect for drinks in the evening. 🥂🎄

It’s fun to go bold in small bathrooms. We divided a bedroom in half to create this space in order to squeeze in a first floor loo. Because of this, we were left with a bathroom with no window. I knew I wanted to incorporate fun wallpaper and bold colour in order to make up for the lack of natural light. I chose this @ottolinedevries wallpaper which has the prettiest colours. I love how it links all the tones from the surrounding rooms together. Half-height t&g panelling adds the element of classicism that I always love in bathrooms. Painted in #aquatic by @edwardbulmerpaint  photo by @chriswakefield.photography 💕🛁

It’s officially Friday, December 1st. I am so looking forward to the holiday season ahead. We have a couple of exciting installs underway as well as a photoshoot of a very cute apartment completed earlier this year. There is so much to do before the end of the year which makes the season approaching even more exciting! 🎄🥂 Is anyone else feeling festive yet?

Another shot of our kitchen in Bath. We used #settingplasterfarrowandball on the cabinetry and love how fresh and fun it feels. We designed this bespoke kitchen from scratch, starting with pen to paper. The aim was for the space to feel characterful and like it had been around for years. Cladding the ceiling in t&g helps with the character of the room. We also chose to incorporate pediments on the top of each alcove unit as a nod to the Georgian city we live in. It is the perfect space for cooking and entertaining. I hope everyone is enjoying a nice Sunday lunch today! 🥬🥦🥕🍋

Corner of our sitting room in Bath feeling very festive. It is such a cosy room to sit in during the winter. The teal grasscloth and curtains envelop the room and make it feel so warm. The perfect backdrop to our art, fabrics and furniture. I hope everyone is getting into the spirit and feeling cosy at home. 🎄🎄✨

A cosy snug room from a project earlier this year. We love designing useable, liveable spaces which are cosy and inviting. This room gets well used by the children and family dog, it was important that it was durable and practical, without compromising on style. The aim was for it to feel timeless and warm. A cosy L-shaped linen sofa with a plethora of cushions fills the room and provides ample seating space for the whole family. We used @farrowandball #denimes on the joinery with #shadedwhite on the walls and #slippersatin on the woodwork. 🤍🤍

A charming corner of a London project's sitting room. Our client is a young American professional who is temporarily residing in London. She really wanted us to make her Victorian rental feel like home. Despite constraints on altering walls and carpet, we filled the space with pretty prints and vibrant colours to break the monotony of beige. We love working on these smaller projects, as they offer quick satisfaction and foster creative thinking. Our goal was to craft a cheerful and cosy home without altering any of the flat's permanent features… perfect for our hip young client. 💕💚💙

Some detail shots of our garland this year. The mantelpiece is the perfect opportunity for going bold with luscious greenery and florals. We filled ours with everything from spruce sprigs and hydrangeas to pomegranates and birds. We then adorned it all with jewel toned ribbon to add the glamour. Hope everyone is feeling the excitement with the build up to Christmas. 🍇🍊🪶🌲

View towards the dining area of our Holland Park rental project. We used fresh pretty colours which were all pulled from the gorgeous @gpjbaker Magnolia fabric. We used this on the antique settee which serves as a dining bench as well as cushions and stools throughout the scheme. The faux bamboo chinese chippendale dining chairs were bought at auction and sprayed Yeabridge Green by @farrowandball and upholstered in a subtle stripe by @janechurchillfabrics this space serves dual function as a dining area and study. Its flooded with natural light. A pair of watermelon curtains frame the huge window and I love the contrast with the neutral walls and carpet. 💕💚🌸🌼🌿

View into the guest loo from the sitting room in our house on Bath. I love a matchy-matchy moment and decided to repeat the fabric from the sitting room as wallpaper in loo. Paired with @edwardbulmerpaint #aquatic on the panelling, the aim was for the very classic print to feel fresh and updated. A modern take on tradition. I’m all about the mix. ❤️💙

Another Christmassy shot of our sitting room this holiday season. This time of year is great when you love colour. I am all about more is more! The tree is layered with ribbons and decorations, which makes our maximalist sitting room even more cosy. It is so nice to enjoy this space in the evening with a glass of bubbles… even Penny dog is enjoying her seat under the tree. 🎄🐶

We were asked by our client to transform her rental apartment in London. This presented a unique challenge as we could not change anything structural. For this reason, we decided to focus the budget on the curtains, upholstery and furniture. These are elements she can take with her when she moves. The brief was to create the feeling of femininity and a sense of home. Being a young woman from New York, our client wanted us to put an English twist on her American aesthetic. The outcome is fun, colourful and young, yet sophisticated. 💕💙🌸🌿

Another view of a hallway installed earlier this year. We knew instantly that this space needed panelling in order to feel finished and to add warmth. We had this installed and painted #slippersatinfarrowandball with #bluegrayfarrowandball on the walls above. The herringbone timber floors instantly add character and glamour to this large space. Inherited brown furniture feel fresh paired with collections of blue and white. 🌿🤍🤎

A joyful and colourful corner of a recent sitting room install in London. We sourced a collection of botanical plates and had them framed in glossy olive green faux bamboo frames. We love the pops of colour throughout. It was important we added contrast and visual interest set against the white walls and beige carpet. As this was a rental apartment, the focus of our design was on all the furniture, fabrics and accessories. The palette is fresh and bright, perfect for our young single client. 🌸🌼💙💕

View down the hall towards the stairs in our narrow Victorian hallway in Bath. It is all decked out for the holiday season. We used a @crucialtrading sisal stair runner with a charcoal border to add drama and warmth to the stairs and love it combined with the black and white checkerboard marble tile in the hall from @mandarinstoneofficial A lush garland and fresh wreath on the mirror ass the festive touch 🍊🌲🪶✨
Merry Christmas Eve! I hope everyone is enjoying time with friends and family this holiday season. Spreading holiday cheer from my kitchen to yours. 🍾🍾🎄🎄

We focus on integrating storage in surprising locations. In constructing this bathroom from the ground up, the newly-built wall containing the sink and toilet presented a chance to create a concealed niche behind the mirror, serving as a functional medicine cabinet. The discreet appearance of the bobbin mirror hanging on the wall adds to the secretive feel. To enhance practicality, we included tongue and groove backing to the storage niche for easy wipe-down. This design choice allowed for a leggy basin, contributing to a more spacious feeling to the room. T&g panelling is painted in @edwardbulmerpaint #aquatic with a fun @ottolinedevries wallpaper above. The custom mirror is in #jonquil also by @edwardbulmerpaint Overall, the room brings us so much joy! 💕🐟💕

Earlier this year, we designed a crafting space for a client passionate about creating art and greeting cards. The room features vibrant @manuelcanovasparis prints on the walls and blinds, complemented by eclectic furniture and accessories, reflecting her unique and joyful aesthetic. The perfect spot for sparking creativity. 🎨✨🧡💜

Wishing everyone a happy and healthy New Year! We are so grateful for all of our amazing clients and followers and we cannot wait to see what 2024 has in store! Looking forward to so many exciting projects ahead. 🥂🍾🎊

A little before, during and after… it is so fun to reflect back on the design journey. When we first acquired the property it was a sad and rundown student house. We immediately got to work stripping it back, tearing it apart and bringing it to life. 🔨🪚🧱Who else enjoys seeing the process and behind the scenes?

Corner of a bedroom in our Holland Park Rental project. The brief was to create a space that felt personal and inviting without changing anything structural within the property. We decided to have a window seat made to add warmth and encourage a lovely spot to sit and enjoy. @colefaxandfowler #bowood is always a timeless classic and is perfect for a calm bedroom scheme. 🤍🤍

Thank you @countryhomesmag for featuring one of our fave projects to-date in your February 2024 issue on newsstands now! We had so much fun designing this whimsical and colourful cottage in the Cotswolds for a very cool young client. It brings us so much joy seeing the photos again in print. It feels so bright and energising during this dreary winter’s day. Special thanks to @alisongibbstylingandwriting for the lovely editorial. 🧡🌿🌸

Some more great press for the start of the year! I am thrilled to see our house in the latest issue of @homesandgardensofficial on newsstands now. It was such a labour of love that it makes it so rewarding to see it in print. Special thanks to @vivienneayers_interiors for the fab editorial. 💕💕🥬🐟
We’re all about layering prints and textures…🐆🌴🐅💕💕

A gallery wall can elevate any staircase, as demonstrated in our Somerset project. The framed botanicals, arranged in a grid and encased in painted frames with cream mounts, create a striking and dramatic contrast to the Georgian staircase, embracing simplicity with a bold outcome. 🌿🤍

View into my bedroom in Bath. We used @farrowandball #redearth on the walls and woodwork. I love how warm and cosy this colour feels. It looks great in the evening. Like a big hug! Our fave @schumacher1889 #tigerpalm print looks cute on an antique chair I had recovered with a flouncy gathered skirt. 🌴🐆🌴🧡 By painting the wardrobes into the wall, they don’t feel dominating in the room and I love the softness the fabric panels provide.

More great press! 📖 We are thrilled to see this project from last year included in the February issue of @25beautifulhomesmagazine It was such a fun project to work on with lovely clients who weren’t afraid of colour and pattern. We love how the house flows from room to room. 💛💙🧡 Special thanks to @alisongibbstylingandwriting for such lovely writing. Photos by @chriswakefield.photography
A few shots from a project in West London featured currently in @25beautifulhomesmagazine We had so much fun playing with colour and pattern. It’s joyful and fresh, perfect for our young clients. 💚🧡💙
